The paper discusses distributed deep learning techniques for solving a scientific inverse problem in materials imaging, which involves large-scale computation and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also focuses on optimizing the communication and computation overlap, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses a Fully Convolutional Neural Network for image reconstruction, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of numerical methods for solving partial differential equations, which falls under the category of cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper discusses the use of high-performance computing resources, which falls under the category of cs.SC (Supercomputing).
